*Dispose as a Outcome for Failed Deliveries*


Not every undelivered order should come back.


We=E2=80=99re introducing *Dispose* as a configurable, controlled outcome a=
cross
the platform, spanning business settings, network capabilities, APIs and
the rider app, while ensuring responsibility and decision-making remain
clearly defined.


Until now, failed deliveries were forced into a limited set of outcomes
like *Reattempt* or *RTO*, even when disposal was the correct business
decision.
Why We Built This

Failed deliveries sit at the intersection of operations, cost, and
accountability. The lack of a formal =E2=80=9CDispose=E2=80=9D option led t=
o:

   -

   Forced RTOs where disposal was intended
   -

   Manual interventions and inconsistencies
   -

   Ambiguity in business intent
   -

   Rider responsibility on undelivered orders

What=E2=80=99s New

Businesses can now configure Dispose as a default action for undelivered
orders.


When selected:

   -

   The delivery task is completed as disposed
   -

   No RTO task is created
   -

   Rider can simply dispose off the order
   -

   Disposed will be a new terminal status & same would be updated in webhoo=
k

New parameter =E2=80=9Cforce_dispose=E2=80=9D has been introduced in the AP=
I to support
this.
View API Documentation
<https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/13758726/2s93RKzFtk#0aac3c63-e0d2-4=
e3f-9ac3-ca677ea8f6a8>


Note: Same is supported at Network level configuration.
What This Means For You

   -

   Businesses can explicitly decide when an order should be disposed
   -

   Networks can declare whether they *support* disposal, without owning the
   decision
   -

   Orders can carry disposal intent directly via APIs
   -

   Riders see clear, unambiguous actions in the app
   -

   Applicable only for riders on Pidge application


Dispose is now a *controlled capability*, not an accidental outcome.
What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
